main event: A witness observed an unidentified object in the sky over the vicinity between Davenport and Des Moines, Iowa on October 10, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared as a light that expanded to be solid, varying in brightness and size at times.
The object was described as being brighter than the brightest stars, with a white color.

The object moved left to right, illuminating the area, and exhibited various behaviors such as standing still, changing brightness, changing shape, flashing or flickering, and disappearing and reappearing.
The witness estimated the object to be about 80 feet in diameter and approximately 0.5 miles away.
Multiple witnesses reported similar sightings in the area.
sighted object: a bright, solid object that changed in size and brightness
location: Between Davenport and Des Moines, Iowa
